Ahead of the Kogi and Bayelsa States Governorship elections, the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has appealed to all registered political parties to caution their candidates and supporters against engaging in activities that violates the Electoral Act. Chairman of the Commission, Prof. Mahmood Yakubu made the appeal today at the quarterly consultative meeting with political parties, in Abuja.  Yakubu disclosed that INEC is working with security agencies to ensure that its officials, materials, processes and procedures are adequately protected during the elections. He also seized the opportunity to call on political parties to submit names of their polling agents fouteen days before the elections, for proper accreditation as required by law.  While calling for legislation that would prevent the manipulation of the nation's electoral system, the Chairman, Inter Party Advisory Council(IPAC), Peter Ameh advised representatives of all political parties to act in the interest of the country during the elections.